.TH ANEDEXT 1

.SH NAME

Anedext \- It's an editor for text.

.SH SYNOPSYS

~$ ./anedext [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION

The Anedext text editor is an editor for text, orignally written by Calm1403.

You've two modes, normal and insert; insert is
similar to Vim's replace mode, allowing a use
r to overwrite a file's contents, in addition
to resizing the file if the user wishes to enter
more than what's already there.

Normal mode is also very similar to Vim's, in
that it's used primarly for navigation; to move
right, you press 'l,' with left, you press 'h.'

.SH OPTIONS

There aren't any options per-se; you supply a file name as an argument to the
program on execution.

.SH SEE ALSO

\%vim(1)
